      <h1>Tutorial: Create your own application</h1>

      <h2>Create from template</h2>
      <div class="indent">
        <p>Simply run:</p>

        <pre>grunt create-package:MyName</pre>

        <p>This will create some source files for you with usable code. You'll have a basic running application with a Window.</p>
      </div>

      <h2>Update manifest</h2>
      <div class="indent">
        <p>
          The manifest holds information about your package, like name, description, icon and used resources.
          Update <b>package.json</b> to fit your application.
        </p>
        <p>
          <i>This is not required and can be done later</i>
        </p>
        <p>
          Example with all available entries:
        </p>
        <pre class="code">
{
  // ClassName used in namespaces
  "className":  "ApplicationMyName",

  // If 'false' application will not be loaded or launchable (Optional)
  "enabled":    true,

  // Application description (optional)
  "description":"Application Long Description",

  // Application name
  "name":       "Application Name",

  // Application category (optional)
  "category":   "unknown",

  // Or an array of regext match MIME strings (Optional)
  "mime":       null,

  // Application icon (use ./my-icon.png for icon inside app folder)
  "icon":       "apps/file-manager.png",

  // Allow only one instance ? (Optional)
  "singular":   false,

  // Show a splash screen when loading application (Optional)
  "splash":     false,

  // Array of features to check for (Optional, uses Utils.getCompability())
  "compability":[],

  // A list of files to preload in order to run app
  "preload":    [
    {"src": "main.js", "type": "javascript"},
    {"src": "main.css", "type": "stylesheet"},
    {"src": "foo.js", "type": "javascript", combine: false} // Do not combine this script in 'dist'
  ],

  // For translations of name and description
  "names" : {
    "no_NO" : "Norwegian name"
  }
  "descriptions" : {
    "no_NO" : "Norwegian description"
  }
}
        </pre>
      </div>

      <h2>Install</h2>
      <div class="indent">
        <p>Now run this command to add it to global manifest (make it visible in OS.js)</p>
        <pre>grunt manifest</pre>

        <br />

        <p>And, if you're using dist (prodiction environment)</p>
        <pre>grunt packages:default/MyName</pre>
        <p>"default" is the repository name which is the default</p>
      </div>

